  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-04-14",
    "date": "2020-08-13T14:59:32Z",
    "text": "COVID-19 Graduate Relief Act\n\nThis bill allows students who graduate from institutions of higher education in 2020 to defer payments on their federal student loans for up to three years.\n\nThe Department of Education (ED) may extend deferment eligibility to students who graduate in 2021 and 2022, if ED determines that the anticipated economic impact of the coronavirus (i.e., the virus that causes COVID-19 or another coronavirus with pandemic potential) on these graduates necessitates an extension. ED must consider certain factors, such as recent unemployment statistics from the Bureau of Labor Statistics, when determining whether to extend deferment eligibility to these graduates."
  },
